- The "rank" is determined by the average score of skaters from each nation within the same competition level;
- The "average score" is calculated by averaging the scores of all skaters from the same nation in the same competition level.

- "shining stars" refers to skaters who have performed exceptionally well;
- "accumulated the most points" means the total points scored by the skater across all competitions;
- "in order of their brilliance" means the list is ordered by total points in descending order.

